Package picross

Class Model

  • java.lang.Object
    • picross.Model
  • public class Model
extends java.lang.Object
    Model Class contains the variables behind the working of the game. Contain methods for manipulating the int[][] and labels associated with gameplay.

      • clueCreate

        public void clueCreate​(javax.swing.JPanel panel,
                       javax.swing.border.Border border,
                       boolean top,
                       Controller buttons,
                       Model model)
        Method displays clues on both top and side panels on game board. Uses for loop to change label details and passes label[] index to clueNum method to set its text.
        Parameters:
        panel - Panel passed from View to add the labels created to. Both topPanel and leftPanel will be passed from View.
        border - border passed from View for use on labels.
        top - Boolean value to indicate if method is being called for the top labels, or the left hand side labels.
        buttons - Controller object passed from View to call its clueNum method on each label[] element.
        model - Model object passed from View. Normally this would not be needed as the method is in the Model class, however the specific Model object from View needs to be manipulated.
